{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"629d17a1-6ed8-4b0b-ae81-34080f50d134","content":"There's no workflow file in the current directory. I can still guide you on the changes needed. Here's what to update:\n\n### 1. **Workflow changes** (`.github/workflows/publish.yml`)\n\n**Add OIDC permissions** to your job:\n```yaml\npermissions:\n  id-token: write   # Required for OIDC token\n  contents: read\n```\n\n**Replace** the `dotnet nuget push` step — remove the `--api-key` flag and add `--source` with the trusted publisher URL:\n```yaml\n# BEFORE\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }} --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n\n# AFTER\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\nNo API key is needed — the OIDC token is exchanged automatically by the `dotnet` CLI (requires .NET SDK 9.0.200+).\n\n### 2. **NuGet.org configuration**\n\nOn [nuget.org](https://www.nuget.org), register your repository as a trusted publisher:\n\n1. Go to your package → **Manage** → **Trusted publishers**\n2. Add a new GitHub Actions policy specifying:\n   - **Repository owner** (org or user)\n   - **Repository name**\n   - **Workflow filename** (e.g., `publish.yml`)\n   - Optionally restrict to a specific **branch/tag** or **environment**\n\n### 3. **Remove the secret**\n\nOnce trusted publishing works, delete `NUGET_API_KEY` from your repository secrets.\n\n### Key requirements\n- **.NET SDK ≥ 9.0.200** (first version with NuGet OIDC support)\n- The workflow **environment** (if used) must match what you registered on nuget.org\n\nWould you like me to create or update a specific workflow file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2313abac-2ee8-4d22-97d6-733c311ac8c1","outputTokens":478,"requestId":"6C43:3DCB6E:DD7C65:1119BEE:6A0129CC"},"id":"66326296-7049-42e3-96fc-e8932ba6af6f","timestamp":"2026-05-11T00:59:04.899Z","parentId":"47713397-0a4d-463c-8549-9b656a856e63"}
